{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645799","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645799"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:21:44+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:21:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18136"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18136","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18136"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10850"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78406"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10850","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10850"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18136"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63768"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25244"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25247"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26871"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78406","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78406"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe forearm muscles are found in superficial or deep layers of the anterior and posterior compartments.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following muscles is found in the deep layer?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Flexor digitorum superficialis","Brachioradialis","Extensor carpi radialis longus","Supinator","Pronator teres"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe forearm muscles are arranged in superficial, intermediate and deep layers within anterior (flexor) and posterior (extensor) compartments. Understanding their arrangement is crucial for clinical assessment of forearm injuries.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESupinator\u003C/strong\u003E is found in the deep posterior compartment of the forearm. It wraps around the proximal radius and is the primary muscle responsible for supination of the forearm when the elbow is extended.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBrachioradialis\u003C/strong\u003E is located in the superficial anterior compartment. While it can assist with both supination and pronation, its main function is elbow flexion, particularly when the forearm is in mid-pronation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlexor digitorum superficialis\u003C/strong\u003E is found in the superficial anterior compartment and flexes the proximal interphalangeal joints of the fingers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtensor carpi radialis longus\u003C/strong\u003E is located in the superficial posterior compartment and extends and abducts the wrist.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPronator teres\u003C/strong\u003E is found in the superficial anterior compartment and is the primary muscle for forearm pronation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The supinator muscle is found in the deep posterior compartment of the forearm and functions to supinate the forearm.","The brachioradialis muscle is found in the superficial anterior compartment of the forearm and functions primarily in elbow flexion."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System (Vol. 1). Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63768"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18136"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63768","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63768"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-10T16:29:58+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-10T16:30:27+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10850"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78406"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"headi